        <div class="mechanism-points">
          <div class="point"><h4><span class="point-num">1.</span>Supports the body's stress response.</h4><p>Rhodiola is studied for its role in supporting the HPA axis, the system that regulates how the body responds to physical and mental stress.</p></div>
          <div class="point"><h4><span class="point-num">2.</span>Helps maintain balanced cortisol.</h4><p>Research suggests Rhodiola helps the body maintain a balanced cortisol response, which plays a role in how energy and focus hold up across long days.</p></div>
          <div class="point"><h4><span class="point-num">3.</span>Supports mental endurance under fatigue.</h4><p>Multiple human trials have studied Rhodiola for its effects on mental performance during periods of fatigue, including shift work and high-demand cognitive tasks.</p></div>
          <div class="point"><h4><span class="point-num">4.</span>Active compounds: salidroside and rosavin.</h4><p>The standardized extract used in research delivers specific levels of salidroside and rosavin, the two compounds most studied for Rhodiola's adaptogenic effects.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="mechanism-footnote">Summarized from published research on Rhodiola Rosea and stress adaptation.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="split">
      <img class="split-image" src="{{ 'rhodiola-rosea-cluster.webp' | asset_url }}" alt="Rhodiola Rosea compound detail" width="1466" height="1084" loading="lazy" />
